  "local_port": 39012,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "A shop was selling 3 chocolates for Re. 1 and if you return three wrappers you get 1 free. If so, how many chocolates can you get for Rs. 45?",
  "response": "Let's break down the process step by step to determine how many chocolates you can get for Rs. 45.\n\n1. **Initial Purchase:**\n   - You buy 3 chocolates for Re. 1.\n   - For Rs. 45, you can buy:\n     \\[\n     45 \\times 3 = 135 \\text{ chocolates}\n     \\]\n\n2. **Wrappers from initial purchase:**\n   - You have 135 wrappers from the 135 chocolates.\n\n3. **Using wrappers to get free chocolates:**\n   - For every 3 wrappers, you get 1 free chocolate.\n   - You can exchange:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{135}{3} = 45 \\text{ free chocolates}\n     \\]\n   - Now you have 45 more chocolates.\n\n4. **New wrappers from free chocolates:**\n   - The 45 free chocolates give you 45 more wrappers.\n   - Using these 45 wrappers, you can exchange:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{45}{3} = 15 \\text{ free chocolates}\n     \\]\n   - Now you have 15 more chocolates.\n\n5. **New wrappers from these additional free chocolates:**\n   - The 15 free chocolates give you 15 wrappers.\n   - Using these 15 wrappers, you can exchange:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{15}{3} = 5 \\text{ free chocolates}\n     \\]\n   - Now you have 5 more chocolates.\n\n6. **New wrappers from these free chocolates:**\n   - The 5 free chocolates give you 5 wrappers.\n   - Using these 5 wrappers, you can exchange:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{5}{3} = 1 \\text{ free chocolate} \\text{ (with 2 wrappers remaining)}\n     \\]\n   - Now you have 1 more chocolate. Total chocolates now include this additional one.\n\n7. **Final count of chocolates:**\n   - Sum all the chocolates obtained:\n   \\[\n   135 \\text{ (initial purchase)} + 45 + 15 + 5 + 1 = 201 \\text{ chocolates}\n   \\]\n\nThus, with Rs. 45, you can get a total of 201 chocolates, taking into account the free chocolates received by returning wrappers.",
